 http://mushroom.sourceforge.net
 Created by: Mark Holloway <molasses@ihug.com.au>
             David Voswinkel


 OVERVIEW ---------------------------------------------------------------------

 Mushroom is a simple C library for the Nintendo Game Boy Advance.
 It provides a thin layer over the GBA hardware to allow for maximum
 control and flexibility in development.

 Mushroom GBALib is public domain. See below for details.


 USING MUSHROOM ---------------------------------------------------------------

 See mushroom.html for information on how to create a new project with
 Mushroom.


 COMPILING THE LIBRARY --------------------------------------------------------

 Requirements:
     DevKitAdvance
     gfx2gba
     Doxygen
     GNU/Linux (or other Unix (Windows may require more makefile editing))

 Set your GCC_DIR in the makefile:
 <mushroom>/build/Makefile_defines

 Enter the directory <mushroom>/src and type:

 make

 The library (libmushroom.a) should then be created in
 <mushroom>/lib.


 OTHER MAKE RULES -------------------------------------------------------------

 make doc                 Generate documentation
 make dist                Clean, compile, make docs and make a tarball
 make clean               Remove lib and .o files
 make distclean           Remove all previously generated files
 make tests               Compile all the tests in the test suite
 make runtests            Run all the tests one after the other
 make cleantests          Remove all generated test suite files


 DIRECTORY STRUCTURE ----------------------------------------------------------

 <mushroom>/
     build/
         doxygen/         Files for creating documentation
         temp/            Temporary files used in compiling

     data/                Graphics data. Default font
     doc/                 Mushroom API Documentation
     include/
         mushroom/        Mushroom header files

     lib/                 The library (libmushoom.a)
     samples/             Sample Mushroom projects
     src/                 The source files of Mushroom
     tests/               Mushroom test suite

     COPYING              License information for Mushroom
     NEWS                 List of changes to Mushroom
     README               Some kind of attempt at documentation


